-- Greek State Employees to Hold Walkout Today on Pension Reforms
-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 2012-07-24T06:46:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-24/greek-state-employees-to-hold-walkout-today-on-pension-reforms.html
Greece’s federation of civil
servants unions, known as ADEDY, will hold a walkout today from
12:30 p.m. to oppose pension cuts requested by the European
Union,  International Monetary Fund  and European Central Bank in
exchange for the country’s bailout.  ADEDY will hold a protest rally outside the Labor Ministry
in Athens at 1 p.m., according to a press release posted on the
union’s website.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
